LBNL/DOE-authored research software typically requires a specific modified
BSD 3-Clause license with copyright held by "The Regents of the University
of California, through Lawrence Berkeley National Laboratory," and may
require registration with LBNL's Innovation & Partnerships Office (IPO)
before public release.

